honesty, the Bidding Days are a bit wild and rowdy,<br>
and while all of my potential buyers are kind, none <br>
of them love me yet.  They only hear that a servant<br>
of Solusek Ro is up for the bid, and all of them would<br>
rip their lungs out (a true horror for Bards) to have<br>
a Fiery girl as their mistress!&quot;  I winked a violet eye.<br>
<br>
Suddenly, Lieutenant Arathur, high commander of<br>
the Qeynos Guard, stepped into Fish's Ale with a <br>
purposeful stride.  As soon as he saw me, he glared.<br>
<br>
&quot;Chrysothemis of Ro, you shall pay for your pride,&quot;<br>
he said sternly.  &quot;Certain members of the Academy<br>
of Arcane Science in Freeport have sealed a pact<br>
with you.  You are to find a Paladin of Mithaniel Marr<br>
and duel him.  Such a paladin, you have heard, bears<br>
an Insignia of Mithaniel that you are to have if you win.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;That is true,&quot; I gasped, out of breath.  &quot;Banegrivm<br>
Shadowblight here has that very same badge, and I<br>
have decided not to brandish my dagger against him.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Very well,&quot; growled Arathur, &quot;but even so, he is not<br>
the one you were destined to duel.  It is I you will <br>
fight, and I'll prove it.  What metal did the Wizards<br>
say that this Insignia of Mithaniel was made of?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;The finest platinum,&quot; I purred, my voice filled with<br>
arrogance.  Then I choked, startled.  &quot;Sir Banegrivm<br>
has a gold one!&quot; I trembled at Arathur.  His Insignia,<br>
shining boldly, was made of pure, gleaming platinum.<br>
<br>
&quot;It is I you will fight.&quot;  The Lieutenant's voice rang <br>
with authority, and the drunken rogues shook!<br>
<br>
Raising my head haughtily, I declared, &quot;We will<br>
duel.  Such a fight can only take place in the arena,<br>
the red Grounds of Fate, under the hot gaze of the <br>
Warlord, Rallos Zek!&quot;   <br>
<br>
&quot;Done!&quot; Lieutenant Arathur's voice now boomed out<br>
with power.  &quot;If you win this fight, fiery Bard, great<br>
Miss Chrysothemis of Ro, you shall win my Insignia<br>
to take back to your Wizard friends in the Academy.<br>
If you lose, haughty one, you shall humble yourself<br>
before all in the arena and prostrate yourself in the <br>
dust.&quot;  His wager contained an air of inexorability.<br>
<br>
I placed my hand in his.  &quot;At votahct!&quot; I cried.  This<br>
was said to be Solusek Ro's declaration of war when he began burning Tunaria, now known as Antonica.  &quot;At&quot;,<br>
in the ancient Flame Tongue, meant &quot;it,&quot; and &quot;votahct,&quot;<br>
a half-verb and half-noun, was the ultimate cry of &quot;War!&quot;,<br>
second only to Rallos Zek's great shout of battle. <br>
<br>
&quot;At votacht,&quot; muttered Arathur, with grudging respect.<br>
He took my arm fiercely, which duelers did to ensure<br>
that neither one turned a coward and fled.  Behind<br>
us came Klieb Torne, Micc Koter, the Ranamers, and<br>
Trumpy Irontoe, plus other patrons of Fish's Ale and <br>
the bouncer, Ragna Sehjar.  We were a fine parade!<br>
<br>
I wasn't sure that Banegrivm would come.  Just as<br>
well.  I suspected it was against nature to view such<br>
inherently proud things as duels, except...he might<br>
come, I thought, to see me win, and to see the great<br>
Lieutenant Arathur brought low if...when...he lost! :-)<br>
